                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3197&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pacification</a> is actually less efficient than <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3359&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Word of Morell</a>, and takes more mana to cast.
<br />

<br />
Personally, the primary reason I got Mez Mastery was to save mana.  Without mez mastery, in order to recharm a pet and get him back into action quickly, I would have to cast <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3359&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Word of Morell</a>, followed by <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3342&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Howl of Tashan</a>, followed by <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4408&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Color Cloud</a>, and then I could cast <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3355&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Command of Druzzil</a> to recharm.  By increasing the duration of WoM, I am able to skip <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=4408&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Color Cloud</a> completely, saving 350 mana per recharm.
<br />

<br />
I have a pretty massive mana pool to begin with, and I am very efficient, but I know I have many options, and I often use them all.  In LDoN, for example, I usually pull/charm/slow/mez/root/nuke/etc. The rest of my group usually gets bored (except for the cleric, cause I also pull with <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1704&source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Winds of Tashanian</a>).
<br />

<br />
In the end, the usefullness of this AA really depends on how you play.  If you just sit back, buff your group, and occasionlly cast a mez when your puller brings an extra mob... then no, this AA will do nothing for you.  However, if you're an impatient freak like me, and view "Full Mana" as a plague to be avoided, then you probably have a playstyle that will make optimal use of this ability.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

