                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Pacification is actually less efficient than Word of Morell, and takes more mana to cast. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Ahhh...blanket statements.   The staple of any good arguement.
<br />

<br />
Pacification can be monstrously more efficient than WoM.  Take a room of 5 mobs. You could:
<br />

<br />
Pull the whole mess at once, and recast WoM approximately 11 times to hold down the whole mess while they are killed (I'm using my experience of how long it takes to kill a single mob - generally slightly less than the duration of a normal mez: I used 48 seconds/mob for this calculation, and assumed that WoM could be counted on to last 18 seconds each time (which is absurd, but I'm giving WoM the benefit of the doubt here)) for a total of 3300 mana to control those 5 mobs.
<br />

<br />
Or you could pacify the middle mobs (most rooms are 'linked' together by one or at most two mobs) - we'll say two, for the sake of arguement, thereby splitting the room into a pull of two and a pull of three. This costs 700 mana to pacify, then 300 mana for the two pull (One cast of bliss) then 900 mana (one cast of bliss on one mob, two casts of bliss on the other) for the three pull. (Note that there is no situation in which you would actually USE bliss for this, but it makes the numbers prettier.): total mana cost - 1900.  
<br />

<br />
Even with Mez Mastery, using WoM to lock mobs down for more than 30 seconds or so is a waste of mana.  Even with 5 mobs (rather unlikely, really)  if you need to recast WoM every 12 seconds to ensure mobs don't get loose,  WoM is equivalently efficient with Bliss (5 mobs with bliss for 60 seconds - 5 casts of bliss, 300 mana each vs. 5 mobs with WoM for 12 seconds x 5 - 5 casts of WoM, at 300 mana each.)
<br />

<br />
Is it a great tool with Mez Mastery? Yes. Is it efficient for any sort of longterm lock down? No.
<br />

<br />
Use all the tools at your disposal. Not just one because it's new, cool, or easy.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
	<tr>
