                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">However, I rarely find pacification to be worth the spell slot, let alone worth the mana to cast it.
<br />

<br />
Root is a viable alternative to mez in most places.
<br />
Proximity agro has less assist range than casting on a mob.
<br />

<br />
I suppose I'm used to pulling with some distance, and using a pet to split agro on a room full of mobs.
<br />

<br />
A room of 6 mobs, I'd pull with using aproximately 2.2k mana.  (using bliss in this example just to be consistant, but for optimal efficiency, sleep would be ideal)
<br />
140 mana: pull with root
<br />
140 mana: root 2nd (target toggle is good)
<br />
0 mana: send in pet to distract the 4 remaining
<br />
0 mana: sit down to pull 3 off my pet
<br />
300 mana: WoM when they get in melee range
<br />
300 mana: Mez one (tho sleep would be better, and 25 less mana)
<br />
0 mana: Group engages one
<br />
100 mana: Move away and slow (tepid) the one the group engages
<br />
140 mana: When wom wears off, root the last one out of melee range
<br />
300 mana: assist pet and mez, pet joins group.
<br />
280 mana: root the 2 mezed
<br />
500 mana: slow remaining 5 mobs in order, no recast needed.
<br />
2200 mana total.
<br />

<br />
Granted, this takes alitte more precision and timing to pull off, but with alittle practice it isn't that difficult.  For LDoN, I find mez and root to be far more reliable than pacify.  I'm not interested in slowing down the fight, nor am I interested in avoiding agro.  Those have a time and place, but unless absolutely necessary, I'm going to push onward.
<br />

<br />
If you have someone in your group who can snare, or dot (and mobs don't summon), this gives them the opportunity to do that ahead of time.  Other debuffs can be applied as well.  But the real reason I pull like this, is cause I don't like to leave my charmed pet alone; He tends to get in trouble when I'm not looking.  Hasted/Dual Wielding, he'll tear thru those mobs before root will break or slow wears off in no time, especially if my tank knows to stand opposite my pet.
<br />

<br />
How you pull is completely seperate from whether or not you use Mez Mastery to its fullest.  The biggest and best reason to have it is for when charm breaks.  I can retash, recharm, and still have time to mez another mob before WoM wears off, and that in and of itself, is huge.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

<br />
